variables.value: Oh my, such a handsome boy!\nCan't help but worry about you.
No fortune today?\nWhat a curious child.
You know, it's always the sweet boys like you who get hooked\non fortunes. So? Got a little curiosity after all?
<MNT:NAGUMOHARA> Hospital's the biggest one around.\nEveryone says you're in good hands here.
I heard it's popular because you can see the ocean from the rooms.\nIt's nice, isn't it? Healing for the body and the heart.
I heard some of the doctors here went to <MNT:NAGUMOHARA> Junior High.\nThat school's got some impressive alumni!
The slopes around here are just right for walking.\nThe sea breeze feels so nice and soothing.
Up ahead's the youth football team's practice pitch.\nThey're famous around here. Folks say they play like middle schoolers!
I was out walking the other day and heard a kid from Seagull FC say,\n"We lost to some junior high kids!" Was that you guys?
I saw you rushing into the hospital the other day. Are you okay?\nMoments like that really remind you how important health is.
Those three guys looking after the kids down at the beach...\nWho are they, anyway?
<FLC:MOGEI> from Seagull FC wants to be a novelist.\nMaybe watching the kids play gives her story ideas!
I heard some kids from the local club say they want to be a team\nlike <MNT:NAGUMOHARA> someday!
That health check has me freaking out...\nI don't want to know the results.
A healthy mind makes a\nhealthy body.
If only work didn't get\nin the way.
Might use some of my\nvacation days.
We've gotta be there\nfor the finals!
Key... my key... where is it...
Hmm... I must've dropped it somewhere around here... But where...
Oh! That's my key indeed!\nI can't believe you found it in this big place and all!
Cats 'round here are real friendly.\nGive one a pat, and they light right up.
This town's full o' cats. Real peaceful, huh?\nWhen I first moved here, I couldn't believe how many there were!
Heh heh, look at that\nhappy face.
They say bent-tailed cats catch happiness, like fish on a hook.\nFunny thing is, they say that in other countries too.
Most cats here have curled tails, but they're rare elsewhere.\nI knew that being from outside and all, but my grandkid was shocked!
Long ago, Nagasaki thrived on foreign trade.\nThey say bent-tailed cats came on ships as rat-catchers back then.
Cats're cute no matter where you go.\nJust petting one gives me the will to live!
This area's just right for cat-spotting strolls.\n"Saruku" means wandering around—it's Nagasaki slang.
Long ago, folks thought cats with long tails would turn into werecats.\nBut bent-tailed ones? Said to be harmless.
Good evening.\nRecently, there have been reports of a fake cop\nprowling around this area...
If you see anyone suspicious, be sure to let me know, okay?
Recently, there have been reports of\na fake cop prowling around this area...
If you see anyone suspicious, be sure to let me know, okay?
[次/つぎ]の[目的地/もくてきち]は[海公園/うみこうえん]です。
Ack! Ever since you showed up, the veterans've been on edge.\nPractice got brutal, and I'm totally wiped out...
Ow ow... my hands are covered in blisters from batting drills.\nBut I'm gonna fill <FLC:YAGYU>'s shoes, no matter what.
The other night, I saw someone training alone at the old shipyard.\nMade me realize that getting hurt's no excuse to give up!
Think we've got a shot at nationals this year...?\nI mean, not that I'm doubting us or anything!
I joined the baseball club 'cause I looked up to <FLC:YAGYU>, y'know?\nI still check all his posts on SNS.
Watching <FLC:YAGYU> crush it out there... Man, even the older students\nlooked proud. And weirdly... I felt proud too.
Her radiant smile made\nit all worth it.
The doctors and nurses really are as kind as people said.\nI'm glad we chose this hospital.
Visiting someone too? My wife's here as well.\nTake care of yourself, okay?
If her next test looks good, she'll get to come home.\nI'm really grateful to the doctor.
Cupid's Carnival has famous flower fields.\nYou'll get great photos there!
The doctor said Mom's getting way better!\nI can't wait to go out with her again!
I've been praying every day for Mom to get better!\nThe doctor says it's working!
Your mom's in the hospital too? Don't worry! I'll pray for her too!
When Mom's back, we're taking a family trip to a theme park!\nNaniwa Land or Cupid's Carnival... can't decide!
Even a hill's good for\nbuilding strength!
Still got youth on your\nside, though.
Think it's helping me\nheal faster, honestly.
Anywhere you wanna stop\non the way home?
I'd like to pick up\nsome soap.
Even the doctor said\nI'm doing great.
Looks like this'll be\nour last visit here.
Nooo! I don't wanna get\na shot!
I don't care!\nI still hate them!
That's enough! Let's\nget this over with!
Sooo... does that mean\nI get extra snacks?
I really don't wanna\nget that shot...
I'll give you a treat\nwhen it's over.
That old lady told me to "watch out for trouble"...\nNow I'm more freaked about that than my health check results.
She calls out to me every time I walk by...\nStart talkin' and boom—she's sellin' weird jars or somethin'.
The InaTuber I follow's been kinda low-energy lately...\nThink somethin' happened in his personal life?
What if someone plotted to take down <FUL:HARU>?\n...Nah, that's just me bein' paranoid.
Haven't been here before but saw the online reviews.\nHope the doctors are as nice as they say.
The doctors really are as kind as they said.\nAlways ready with a smile. Sure feels nice coming here.
I wanna be a nurse someday.\nThat's why I worked hard to get into <MNT:NAGUMOHARA>.
I heard a bunch of <MNT:NAGUMOHARA> grads work here.\nI'd love to ask how they got ready for it.
They say science is super important if you wanna be a nurse.\nMiss <LST:KASUMISAKI> seems nice. Maybe I'll ask her for math help.
Told me I need a total\nlifestyle overhaul...
I wanna impress 'em at\nmy next checkup...
You think it'll really\nwork like that...?
Let's hit a spot before\nwe bounce.
Glad they liked the\nstuff we brought!
You here for a checkup? Lost my voice lately...\nGet well soon! I've heard the football team's in a tournament...
I've felt weird ever since hearing <FLC:ARIA>'s solo...\nThey say her voice can hypnotize. Think it's true?
I'm feeling way better now, and might just go out for a bite.\nPerhaps noodles at Champon Bluespring, with extra veggies!
Even the literature\nclub told me to join!
